                                        <div1 xml:id="tools">
                                            <head>Arabic NLP Tools</head>
                                            <div2>
                                                <p>While there have not been around many tools to process Arabic language data in the past,
               the situation has definitely changed in recent years. The following list is a first attempt to 
               create a list of tools used by the VICAV crew and other relevant projects.</p>
                                                <div3 xml:id="corpora">
                                                    <head>Corpora</head>
                                                    <p>The number of digitally encoded Arabic language corpora has been on the rise in recent years.
                  Unfortunately, most of these resources are not publicly available.</p>
                                                    <div4 xml:id="CorpAfroAs">
                                                        <head>CorpAfroAs</head>
                                                        <p>
                                                            CorpAfroAs is an integrated pilot project that also produced Arabic data. On the
                                                            <ref target="http://corpafroas.huma-num.fr/">project web site</ref>
                                                            , you can find
                     extensive information on how to build corpora of spoken language. The data is available.
                                                        </p>
                                                    </div4>
                                                    <div4 xml:id="tunisianArabicCorpus">
                                                        <head>Tunisian Arabic Corpus</head>
                                                        <p>
                                                            This is a comparatively large corpus of Tunisian Arabic mainly collected from the Internet.
                     The corpus has a very nice
                                                            <ref target="http://tunisiya.org/">web interface</ref>
                                                            .
                                                        </p>
                                                    </div4>
                                                    <div4 xml:id="moroccanArabicWriters">
                                                        <head>Corpus of Moroccan Arabic Writers of Short Stories and Literary Reviews</head>
                                                        <p>
                                                            Information on this corpus can be found
                                                            <ref target="http://www.ugr.es/~dgb/corpus/">here</ref>
                                                            .
                                                        </p>
                                                    </div4>
